            <title>[CASSANDRA-10361] DropTableStatement do not throw an error if the table is a view</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10361</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While testing cqlsh, I discovered that &lt;tt&gt;DROP TABLE &amp;lt;mv name&amp;gt;;&lt;/tt&gt; was not rejected and that it was corrupting the MV.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12873238">CASSANDRA-10361</key>
